Here I show that it is possible to re-assign a task from automation to human labor following a positive productivity shock in an adjacent task.
 Imagine we have three tasks 1,
 2,
 3,
 and imagine 
\begin_inset Formula $q_{1},q_{2},q_{3}$
\end_inset

 are high such that all tasks are done separately by machine (
